p:metadata.p:property:
Ever since its formation the foundation has undertaken a number of education initiatives which make a difference in the lives of deserving and needy students. The trust has provided
more than Rs. 9, 45,466 in the form of grant, scholarships and loans. KAKKERI FOUNDATION is thus living its vision of transforming the lives of peoples of India through education,
by providing financial assistance and recognition to them, across age group and income strata. We live by our belief that no one should be denied an opportunity due to financial
constraints. You could find many inspiring stories from our scholarship recipients and students who availed our loan facilities.

With a population in excess of one billion people, India accounts for 16 per cent of the world’s population and 21 per cent of the world’s global burden of disease. Since independence,
and buoyed by a healthy economy and a wider acceptance of its presence in the larger world, the country has made substantial gains in the health sector, including increased life
expectancy, reduced infant mortality, reduced fertility rates, eradication of smallpox and reduction of leprosy.

However, disparities do exist between urban and rural confines, between states, between districts within states, and between communities within districts and 80% of the healthcare
need are still being provided by private sector. Currently, the trust provides individual medical grants for patients undergoing allopathic treatment. The applications for grants can be
obtained from the office, which has to be duly filled and submitted to the Trusts by the patient, or any immediate family member of the patient.

p:metadata.p:property:
With a population in excess of one billion people, India accounts for 16 per cent of the world’s population and 21 per cent of the world’s global burden of disease. Since independence,
and buoyed by a healthy economy and a wider acceptance of its presence in the larger world, the country has made substantial gains in the health sector, including increased life
expectancy, reduced infant mortality, reduced fertility rates, eradication of smallpox and reduction of leprosy.

However, disparities do exist between urban and rural confines, between states, between districts within states, and between communities within districts and 80% of the healthcare
need are still being provided by private sector. Currently, the trust provides individual medical grants for patients undergoing allopathic treatment. The applications for grants can be
obtained from the office, which has to be duly filled and submitted to the Trusts by the patient, or any immediate family member of the patient.

Ever since its formation the foundation has undertaken a number of education initiatives which make a difference in the lives of deserving and needy students. The trust has provided
more than Rs. 9, 45,466 in the form of grant, scholarships and loans. KAKKERI FOUNDATION is thus living its vision of transforming the lives of peoples of India through education,

constraints. You could find many inspiring stories from our scholarship recipients and students who availed our loan facilities.

Ever since its formation the foundation has undertaken a number of education initiatives which make a difference in the lives of deserving and needy students. The trust has provided
more than Rs. 9, 45,466 in the form of grant, scholarships and loans. KAKKERI FOUNDATION is thus living its vision of transforming the lives of peoples of India through education,
by providing financial assistance and recognition to them, across age group and income strata. We live by our belief that no one should be denied an opportunity due to financial
constraints. You could find many inspiring stories from our scholarship recipients and students who availed our loan facilities.
